type.name: Feature
type.description: A request, idea, or new functionality

issue.body:
Sometimes code starts out as dealing with 2 patterns in the same way, but then later, something different has to happen for one or all of the cases. It could be nice if the language server provided a code action to split an alternative pattern into individual pattern matches.

Before:

```gleam
case next() {
  Ok(response) -> response
  Error(MissingAccessToken) | Error(MissingRefreshToken) -> unauthorized()
  //  ^ split alternative patterns
}
```

After:

```gleam
case next() {
  Ok(response) -> response
  Error(MissingAccessToken) -> unauthorized()
  Error(MissingRefreshToken) -> unauthorized()
}
```

To consider:
- split The pattern on the selected pipe; That would make it more flexible, but would require more clicks to fully split a pattern.
- Split out only the currently hovered alternative, leaving the rest in place

Created coding-standard.py to check whitespace/formatting of plain text files (#981)

Created coding-standard.py to check whitespace/formatting of plain text files.

The Python script will check text files to make sure they don't have
any tab characters (except Makefiles) and they don't have trailing
whitespace. I made it smarter than the sample pre-commit hook: it
*only checks the files that are being changed*, not the entire
repo. This way there's no huge commit just to update whitespace.

It's also able to do double duty as a PR check. Same thing, it only
checks the files in the PR, not the entire repo. If there's any bad
whitespace then it blocks the PR from being committed.

I've *also* added checking of the C formatting to the
tool. **HOWEVER** it will only check the C++ coding style **IFF** the
previous version of the file in the repo *already* conforms to the
standard as specified by the `.clang-format` file. I suspect there
aren't many files that already conform, if there are any at all, so
it's unlikely anyone will run into complaints about an edited file not
having proper formatting. A brand new file *will* be expected to
conform though. I made a couple of minor changes to the
`.clang-format`: no tab characters, and lines should be less than 96
characters long.

Two other features are `--fix` which will automatically make the
necessary corrections to only the files listed on the command line;
and `--show` that reformats the specified file and prints it to
stdout.

pull_request.title: Milestone: 707 problems (46% of CUTEst) + performance optimizations
pull_request.body:
## Summary
This PR adds 41 new problem implementations and applies critical performance optimizations to the CLEUVEN series, bringing the total to **707 problems (46% of CUTEst)** ðŸŽ‰

## Changes Overview
- **95 files changed**: 8,834 insertions(+), 92 deletions(-)
- **38 new passing problems** 
- **3 problems marked for human review**
- **Performance optimizations** for CLEUVEN series
- **Version bump** to 0.0.6

## New Problems Added

### âœ… Passing (38 problems)
**CLEUVEN series (6)**: CLEUVEN2, CLEUVEN3, CLEUVEN4, CLEUVEN5, CLEUVEN6, CLEUVEN7
- Fixed hashability issues by moving JAX arrays to module level
- Applied segment_sum for sparse matrices (CLEUVEN2: 4.91x runtime)
- Used dense ops for 10.5% density matrices (CLEUVEN7: 1.81x runtime)

**DMN series (4)**: DMN15102, DMN15103, DMN15102LS, DMN15103LS

**FBRAIN series (8)**: FBRAIN, FBRAIN2, FBRAIN2NE, FBRAIN3, FBRAINNE, FBRAIN2LS, FBRAIN3LS, FBRAINLS

**Other problems (20)**: CHARDIS0, FLETCHER, FLT, KIRBY2, KIRBY2LS, KOEBHELB, KOEBHELBNE, KSS, SBRYBND, SROSENBR, SCURLY10, SCURLY20, SCURLY30, SNAIL, SPARSINE, and more

### âŒ Marked for Human Review (3 problems)
- **FCCU**: Objective value discrepancies
- **FEEDLOC**: Constraint dimension mismatch
- **KISSING**: Runtime 5.37x (slightly over 5x threshold)
- **KTMODEL**: Multiple test failures (starting value, bounds, constraints, jacobian)
- **SCHMVETT**: Hessian NaN issue at zero vector

## Key Technical Improvements
1. **Hashability fix**: Moved JAX arrays to module level for JIT compatibility
2. **Sparse optimization**: Applied `segment_sum` for very sparse matrices (<1% density)
3. **Dense optimization**: Used dense matrix multiplication for ~10% density matrices
4. **Data extraction**: Converted CLEUVEN SIF data to NPZ format for better performance
5. **Test infrastructure**: Fixed LOCAL_PATH in run_tests.sh

## Test Results
All 38 new problems pass the full test suite including:
- Correctness tests against pycutest
- Runtime performance tests (< 5x threshold)
- Compilation and JIT tests
- Gradient and Hessian verification

## Performance Highlights
- CLEUVEN2: Optimized from timeout to 4.91x (under 5x threshold)
- CLEUVEN7: Optimized from 6.72x to 1.81x (3.7x improvement)
